##General Style Rules

-Lazy load custom css files. Do not mount them if they are not necessary.

-Unless I say you to use custom css do not use it.

## Use this styling rules for our stylings. Use this rules in tailwind unless I explicitly tell you to use custom css instead (even if I declared the style rules in custom css like rgb() use the tailwind counterpart of them if I did not say to use custom css. The rules might declared in tailwind css if I did not specify to use custom css use tailwind but if I specify to use custom css for them use custom css counterpart of that tailwind rules. ) Do not add any styling to specified elements unless told to you.

#Style Rules

## Primary Button Rules

###Color
-Primary Button Hover Background Color: rgb(0, 100, 0)
-Primary Button Background Color: rgb(0, 128, 0)
-Primary Button Writing Color:rgb(255, 255, 255)

### Typography

-Primary Button Font Weight: font-semibold
-Primary Button Font Size: 1rem
-Primary Button Border Radius: 6px

### Interactive

-Primary Button Cursor: Pointer
-Primary Button Transitions: transition colors

## Link Font Rules

### Text Color

- Link Font Text Color: text-green-500
- Link Font Hover Color: text-green-600

### Typography

- Link Font Size: text-sm
- Link Font Weight: font-normal

### Interactive State

focus:outline-none
focus:underline = text-decoration: underline
cursor-pointer

#### Disabled States

disabled:opacity-50  
disabled:cursor-not-allowed

### Container Styling

-The button is wrapped in a div with:

text-right = text-align: right
mb-3
w-4/5
mx-auto

### Accessibility

-tabIndex="0"
-Proper aria handling through focus states
